    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a really strong angle. people always bring up things like hate speech or misinformation to justify regulation though. if i'm writing this, how should i address those counterarguments? like, should i just argue that the risk of government overreach is always worse than the harm caused by bad speech, or is there a more nuanced way to frame it so it doesn't sound too extreme?",
