      "content": "You should frame it as a matter of principle, not just risk assessment; the potential for government abuse is an absolute, existential threat to liberty. Arguing that the cure (regulation) is worse than the disease (bad speech) is a philosophical necessity, not a mere calculation. To sound nuanced, you must insist that private discourse, even offensive discourse, is the necessary crucible where societal truths are forged, and the state has no right to step into that process.",
